<TITLE> Information secy sued for 'defamation' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 22 (bdnews24.com)  A defamation case has been filed against information secretary ATM Fazlul Karim for writing a poem, using the pen-name of Abu Karim, that gives a derogatory epithet to independence leader Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. Awami Ulama League president Maulana Md Ilias Hossain bin Helali filed the case Sunday with the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court. Magistrate Kanika Biswas asked the plaintiff to produce the collection of poems before the court on March 2. She will give orders on whether the case will be taken into cognisance after reading the poem. The case states that the poem gives 'pejorative' titles to Sheikh Mujib's sons, Sheikh Jamal, Sheikh Kamal and Sheikh Russell. A report on the poem was published in the daily Amader Shomoy on Feb 20. Publisher of the newspaper Naimul Islam Khan has been named a witness in the case. bdnews24.com
